&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Role:  Full Time Practice Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: Negotiable on experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surgery name:  John Tasker House Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Great Dunmow&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Region:  West Essex  CCG&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by experienced members of our team (the departing Practice Manager) and have the benefit and support of a branch manager and IT Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see the attached job spec for full details.   For further information, please contact: annie.taylor@nhs.net  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The salary will be attractive/negotiable depending on the candidate’s experience. And will benefit from the NHS pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  This role is also being advertised on the Essex Primary Care Careers website – please complete only one application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have the right to close the advert earlier if we reach the maximum number of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NO AGENCIES PLEASE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate would be someone with experience as a Practice Manager, or someone with administrative experience in Primary Care, perhaps previously working as an Assistant Practice Manager, who is keen to progress their career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an innovative, enthusiastic, practice working out of a modern, purpose-built surgery, with a branch surgery at our Felsted location. We have four partners and seven salaried doctors with a list size of 15,000 patients. We are a training practice and have three registrars in training.&lt;/p&gt;
